The paper presents a deep generative model for machine translation using neural networks and variational inference. This work is highly relevant to the field of natural language processing (NLP) and specifically machine translation, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of neural networks and variational inference also suggests a strong connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the statistical implications of joint modelling, which could be relevant to the field of statistics and machine learning (cs.NE). Finally, the paper mentions the use of synthetic data, which could be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and other areas of machine learning.
